commentTextItems.html: that's it England win, short ball, Vaughan pulls to the midwicket fence.

commentPostTextItems.html: England win by 9 wickets, a comprehensive win.
Please join us again on the 10th of July for the second match of the NatWest Challenge.
Man of the Match: ME Trescothick

commentTextItems.html: played to the deep square leg region for a couple of runs.

commentTextItems.html: full toss, driven down the ground to long-on.
tossed up, full toss, turned to Ponting at midwicket.
tossed up, pitched outside leg stump, played to short fine leg.
pitched up, Vaughan moves to the leg side and thrashes it to the extra-cover fence.

commentTextItems.html: yorker! Vaughan digs it out to the off side.
100! for Trescothick, drives it wide off the mid-off fielder to deep extra-covers, not well timed, Good hundred for Trescothick.
pitched up, driven on the up past the mid-on fielder to the long-on fence.
yorker! Trescothick steps down the track, gets beaten.
Trescothick on the back-foot plays to the backward-point region.
